ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; CARWASH WILL BENEFIT ESTANCIA'S KEY CLUB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM RAGAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A carwash from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. today at a local gas station will help raise 
money for Estancia High School's Key Club, an organization that helps the 
elderly and the homeless. 
</P>
<P>
 The washes will cost $2.The club, which has been in existence for 25 years, 
gets 50 cents per vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
 Alexander Zaslavski, the owner of Your Neighborhood Service Station at El 
Camino and Mendoza drives, said students will be volunteering as driers to 
service the cars as they come out of his automated wash and wax. 
</P>
<P>
 "It will raise some money for a good cause," said Zaslavski, a Russian 
immigrant who came to the United States 16 years ago and is trying to make it 
in the gasoline station business. 
</P>
<P>
 The high school's principal, Peggy Anatol, praised the club members. 
</P>
<P>
 "This gives them a purpose and a chance to work in the community," she said. 
"It helps them to realize the bigger picture in life. Working on the weekends 
is commendable."TOM RAGAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
