<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA HABRA; FREE HOME BUYERS WORKSHOP PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The La Habra Neighborhood Housing Services is inviting low-income people to 
attend a free home buyers workshop Sept. 17 in the La Habra City School 
District office. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone who completes the workshop, which will cover how to apply for a loan 
and how to budget monthly expenses, will be eligible to apply for special home 
loans, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 To qualify, prospective home buyers' family incomes must be less than the 
average family income in Orange and Los Angeles counties -- that is, about 
$64,000 for a family of four in Orange County and about $53,000 for a family of 
four in Los Angeles County. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop will be at 9 a.m. at the district office building, 500 N. Walnut 
St. Spanish interpretation will be available. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (310) 694-2051. MIMI KO 
</P>
</TEXT>
