<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; BARBECUE TO BENEFIT ABUSED CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A country-Western barbecue and silent auction will take place today in Santa 
Ana Heights to raise money for abused children. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is sponsored by Family Service of Orange County and ARK, Services 
for Abused Children, both local nonprofit groups that aid troubled youngsters. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $75 each, and the proceeds will be shared by each organization. 
</P>
<P>
 The country-Western group Out on Bail will perform, and Kim Petyo formerly of 
the Country Rock Cafe, will offer dance instruction.  
</P>
<P>
 Auction-goers can bid for more than 80 items, including a trip to Bora Bora, a 
cruise, dinners, artwork and jewelry. Many of the opening bids will be as low 
as $10 to $50. 
</P>
<P>
 "It is going to be a first-class party," said Monica Milstead of ARK. 
</P>
<P>
 The Crean mansion at 2300 Mesa Drive, owned by John and Donna Crean, is behind 
the Newport Beach Golf Club and overlooks Newport's Back Bay. The fund-raiser 
will be from 4 to 9 p.m.  
</P>
<P>
 Tickets will be available at the event, but participants should first call ARK 
at (714) 978-0340 and leave a message that they plan to attend. LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</TEXT>
