<P>
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA FILE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROSANNE KEYNAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 DATES 
</P>
<P>
 * Social justice will be the theme of the Rev. Grayson Warren Brown's 
four-evening Bible study course at St. Mary's Church in Palmdale. The sessions 
will take place from 7:30 p.m. to 9 p.m. Monday through Thursday. A donation of 
$35 is requested for all four evenings. 1600 E. Ave. R-4. For information or 
registration, (805) 947-3306. 
</P>
<P>
 * "Loneliness From a Christian Point of View" is the topic psychotherapist 
Richard Allen Fraser will address at the Prime Time Singles Midweek Fellowship 
of Arcadia Presbyterian Church at 7:30 p.m. Wednesday. 121 Alice St. (818) 
445-7470. 
</P>
<P>
 * "See You at the Pole" is the National Network of Youth Ministries' campus 
prayer campaign, scheduled for Wednesday, Sept. 21. Students will gather around 
school flagpoles across the country at 7 a.m. for student-led prayer. For 
information, (619) 592-9200. 
</P>
<P>
 * Christ the Shepherd Evangelical Lutheran Church in Altadena will celebrate 
the fifth anniversary of joining the Reconciled in Christ programs of Lutherans 
Concerned at a 10:30 a.m. Eucharist on Sept. 18. The organization supports full 
acceptance and participation of gay men and lesbians in the church. Ron 
Brasgalla, regional representative of the Reconciled program, will speak, and 
members of the Gay Men's Chorus of Los Angeles will sing. 185 W. Altadena Drive 
(818) 794-7011. 
</P>
<P>
 * Six organists will perform in a recital at Trinity Evangelical Lutheran 
Church in Long Beach on Sunday at 4 p.m. The organists are Sean O'Neal, parish 
organist, Charlotte Bellamy, Marc Dickey, Karlene George, Mark Milleran and 
David York. A donation of $8 for adults and $6 for seniors will be asked. 
Proceeds will go toward completion of a 42-rank organ. 759 Linden Ave. (310) 
437-4002. 
</P>
<P>
 HONORED 
</P>
<P>
 The Rev. Diana Heath of Cincinnati, Ohio, has been named minister of Orange 
Coast Unitarian Universalist Church in Costa Mesa. She will deliver her first 
sermon during 10:30 a.m. services Sunday. 1259 Victoria St. (714) 965-1176. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rev. Roger Barkey has been named senior pastor of Congregational Church of 
Northridge. He will deliver his first sermon at 10 a.m. services Sunday. 9659 
Balboa Blvd. (818) 349-2400. 
</P>
<P>
 Lisa Edwards last month was appointed rabbi of Beth Chayim Chadashim in Los 
Angeles, the nation's oldest synagogue serving gay, lesbian and bisexual 
communities. 
</P>
<P>
 BRIEFLY 
</P>
<P>
 * Catholic Big Brothers is seeking volunteer men of all faiths throughout Los 
Angeles County to serve as role models to boys 7 to 14 who come from 
single-parent families and various religious backgrounds. Volunteers are 
screened and must commit at least three hours a week to a youngster. The 
organization also operates the largest program of its kind in the nation for 
hearing-impaired boys and girls ages 6 to 18. Catholic Big Brothers is a United 
Way agency affiliated with Big Brothers/Big Sisters of America, with offices 
throughout Southern California. The staff can answer questions in English and 
Spanish and for the hearing-impaired. (213) 251-9800. 
</P>
<P>
 * The Zen Mountain Center, 120 miles east of Los Angeles in the San Jacinto 
Mountains, has a full roster of fall retreats and other activities for 
beginners to advanced practitioners of Zen. For information, (909) 659-5272. 
ROSANNE KEYNAN 
</P>
