WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; AMTRAK OKS FREE STOPS AT STATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After months of wrangling over the cost of providing Amtrak service to 
Camarillo, the rail carrier has agreed to stop at the station free of charge. 
</P>
<P>
 Amtrak withdrew its request for $150,000 in track and station improvements 
after a series of discussions with members of the Ventura County Transportation 
Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission began working to bring Amtrak trains to Camarillo shortly after 
a temporary station was built to serve commuters riding Metrolink trains in the 
wake of the Jan. 17 earthquake. SARA CATANIA 
