EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; BANK TELLER ROBBED 2ND DAY ON THE JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 22-year-old bank teller during her second day on the job was robbed by a 
well-dressed man who simulated having a gun Friday morning at a Bank of America 
branch in Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 "Welcome to the bank business," said Sgt. Bob Gardner of the Simi Valley 
Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, dressed in slacks, dress shirt and tie and wearing a baseball cap and 
sunglasses, entered the bank at 5821 Los Angeles Ave. about 10:20 a.m., Gardner 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 When he stepped up to the teller, he put a fanny pack on the counter and 
placed his hand inside as if he had a weapon, the sergeant said. The man, 
believed to be in his early to mid-30s, received an undisclosed amount of money 
before fleeing on foot. 
</P>
<P>
 The robber was described as black, about six feet tall and weighing 180 to 200 
pounds, Gardner said. GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
