<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: PROPERTY ASSESSMENT APPEALS DUE SOON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County property owners dissatisfied with the county's assessment of 
their property values have until Thursday to file an appeal. 
</P>
<P>
 The requests to lower taxable values must be filed with the clerk of the 
Assessment Appeals Board at 800 S. Victoria Ave. by 5:30 p.m. or be postmarked 
by Sept. 15.Forms may be obtained from the appeals board or the county 
assessor's office. 
</P>
<P>
 Already, the county has received nearly 2,000 appeals -- more than twice the 
number filed last year. Many of those appeals were filed by oil companies and 
the Bank of America. 
</P>
<P>
 The bank filed 515 appeals on parcels it owns in the financially troubled Wood 
Ranch development in Simi Valley. The bank contends the county assessor has 
overvalued the lots, most of which sit vacant. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
