<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: MOORPARK BACKS BID FOR VOTE ON LANDFILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Moorpark City Council voted 4 to 1 to support a bid to put the Weldon 
Canyon landfill initiative back on November's ballot. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark is the first city to vote in support of the appeal, filed by Taconic 
Resources of San Diego, of a Superior Court ruling that removed the initiative 
from the ballot.The judge ruled that the initiative was being misused to grant 
land rights to a private firm and would create inconsistencies in county zoning 
laws. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilman Scott Montgomery, who voted with the majority, said he expected 
other cities to take similar action. 
</P>
<P>
 "Only Ojai and Ventura supported taking that off the ballot," he said. "There 
are eight other cities and I expect all eight or very close to that number to 
vote for an appeal." SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
