<HEADLINE>
<P>
'FRAGILE ECOLOGIES' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Of all the exhibits at all the festivals, galleries and studios etc. in 
Laguna, there is only one that must be experienced by people who profess 
opinions about and concerns for our environment. That show is "Fragile 
Ecologies: Artists' Interpretations and Solutions" at the Laguna Art Museum. 
</P>
<P>
 It seems to me that the protective-reactive attitudes of those of us concerned 
about the invasion of development have blocked our abilities to think 
creatively in making an evolving urban area somewhat compatible with, and 
mitigated by, our beautiful natural environment and the resources at hand. 
</P>
<P>
 One hopes that this stultified vision can be awakened somewhat by the "Fragile 
Ecologies" exhibition so that new possibilities may enter the thinking of the 
environmentally concerned. All the transformation that can be mustered, as well 
as resolve, are going to be needed. 
</P>
<P>
 ANDY WING 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
