<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: NFL '94: JUST DO THE WAVE TO YOUR WALLET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The tab for taking in a National Football League game will average $184 for 
four people this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Team Marketing Report of Chicago, which tracks pro sports admission prices, 
says the average ticket price has reached $31.04 and the cost of an NFL outing 
is up 6% from last year. Green Bay Packer fans get the best deal: For $151.02 
they can get four tickets, two beers, four soft drinks, four hot dogs, two 
souvenir caps, two programs and parking. San Francisco 49ers fans would pay 
$236 for a similar outing. 
</P>
