<HEADLINE>
<P>
WITNESSES RECANT TESTIMONY, FREE DEATH ROW INMATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Death Row inmate awaiting retrial was freed Thursday, two months after the 
main witnesses against him recanted their testimony and one confessed to the 
crime. 
</P>
<P>
 Joseph Burrows, who was sentenced to death five years ago, was released on a 
recognizance bond and given a send-off by his fellow inmates. 
</P>
<P>
 Burrows, 41, was one of three people convicted of killing William Dulin in 
1988. The other two -- Gayle Potter and Ralph Frye -- received lighter 
sentences in exchange for their testimony. But Potter and Frye recanted their 
testimony during a July hearing. Potter said she alone killed Dulin. 
</P>
<P>
 Last week, a Circuit Court judge overturned Burrows' conviction and ordered a 
new trial. 
</P>
