<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: FREE SHUTTLE TO VA HOSPITAL EXPANDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Free shuttle service for veterans needing transportation to and from the 
Sepulveda Veterans Administration Hospital has been expanded to veterans 
residing in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 The shuttle, provided by the Disabled American Veterans, already serves 
clients in Simi Valley, Lancaster and the San Fernando Valley.The four vans are 
driven by volunteers. 
</P>
<P>
 "We realize a lot of people don't have money . . . or they don't have 
transportation," said Marie Williams, transportation coordinator for Disabled 
American Veterans. "We do our best to get them over here" to the North Hills 
hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 The shuttle service is available Mondays through Fridays from 7 a.m. to 2 p.m. 
Reservations must be made three days in advance. To schedule a ride, call the 
following numbers: from the San Fernando Valley, (818) 891-7711, Ext. 9145, or 
895-9408; from Simi Valley, (805) 526-9237; from Lancaster, (805) 947-0448, and 
from Ventura, (805) 385-8500. JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
