</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Auto Racing 
</P>
<P>
 Jean Alesi won the provisional pole position for Sunday's Italian Grand Prix 
in Monza , Italy, edging British favorite Damon Hill by 0.114 seconds in the 
opening round of qualifying. 
</P>
<P>
 Ted Musgrave broke his own track mark to earn the top starting spot for 
Saturday night's Miller Genuine Draft 400 in Richmond, Va.Musgrave needed just 
21.765 seconds to guide his Ford Thunderbird to a record-setting lap. His lap 
translated into a speed of 124.052 m.p.h., safely ahead of the 123.474 mark he 
set March 4. Miscellany 
</P>
<P>
 The U.S. women's water polo team lost to Italy, 14-9, in the bronze medal game 
of the world championships in Rome. Also, the U.S. men enhanced their chances 
for a sixth-place finish by tying Hungary, 11-11. 
</P>
