<P>
YANCEY SERVED AS EDUCATOR FOR MANIC DEPRESSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Golfer Bert Yancey, who died last week, had the courage to help educate the 
public about manic depression, which provided a much-needed service and 
awareness. 
</P>
<P>
 Because Yancey's heart attack and the symptoms that preceded it were not taken 
seriously, it is obvious there needs to be more public awareness about heart 
disease and the specific warning signs of a heart attack. 
</P>
<P>
 SUSAN LESLIE SMITH 
</P>
<P>
 San Marino 
