<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; YUGOSLAVIA; U.N. TAKES STEPS TO EASE EMBARGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The United States and European nations are drafting a U.N. resolution to ease 
sanctions against Yugoslavia in return for its cutoff of non-humanitarian aid 
to Bosnian Serbs. Speaking on condition of anonymity, diplomats said Friday 
that the sanctions could be relaxed because the Yugoslav government agreed to 
the stationing of foreign civilian monitors along its border with 
Serb-controlled parts of Bosnia. Likely first steps would include reopening the 
airport in Belgrade to international flights and international sports and 
cultural contacts. 
</P>
