<P>
ISRAEL TO RELEASE 127 PALESTINIANS CONFINED TO JERICHO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Israel will allow 127 Palestinians it has confined to the Palestinian 
self-rule enclave in the West Bank town of Jericho to return to their homes 
within a week, Israeli security sources said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 "Forty-one have already been allowed home, and 127 more will go within a 
week," one security source said. 
</P>
<P>
 The freed men, barred from home and stuck in Jericho with nothing to do, have 
become a source of friction between Israel and the Palestinian Authority 
running self-rule. Jericho residents have demonstrated alongside the men 
demanding that they be allowed home. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the May 4 accord setting up self-rule in Jericho and the Gaza Strip, 
Israel pledged to free 5,000 Palestinian prisoners. Most have been released. 
</P>
<P>
 Israel forced about 550 freed Palestinians it had convicted of certain 
offenses who had homes elsewhere in the West Bank to stay in Jericho until 
their sentences ran out. 
</P>
