<HEADLINE>
<P>
TAFT GETS PASSED BY CRESPI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VINCE KOWALICK, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One back-breaking run by tailback Jerry Brown usually is all it takes for Taft 
High to polish off an opponent. 
</P>
<P>
 But Brown's 96-yard, third-quarter touchdown dash only set the stage for a 
dramatic comeback, as Crespi scored 14 consecutive points to claim a 20-19 
victory Friday night at Pierce College. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior quarterback Dave Lins led the Celts on touchdown drives of 68 and 37 
yards to overcome a 19-6 deficit that Taft opened with two touchdowns early in 
the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Lins scrambled eight yards for a touchdown late in the third quarter, then 
connected with Jeff DeFinney for a 20-yard touchdown with 8 minutes 5 seconds 
to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Lins, who threw an eight-yard touchdown pass to Marcos Solorzano in the second 
quarter, completed 21 of 27 for 210 yards. Under pressure throughout the game, 
Lins was sacked four times and had a pass intercepted and returned 26 yards for 
a touchdown by linebacker Antuan Simpson in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 But like his teammates, Lins rebounded. "We never give up," Lins said. "We 
have a lot of heart. We showed some pride." 
</P>
<P>
 Brown, among the best backs in Southern California, rushed for 172 yards in 14 
carries and appeared to give the Toreadors a comfortable lead with his 
coast-to-coast dash that came one play after Lins was stacked up on fourth down 
inside the five-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown accounted for 21 yards on Taft's opening drive, as the Toreadors marched 
57 yards in seven plays to take a 7-0 lead. Quarterback Dayon Shaw connected 
with Dashon Polk for completions of 17, 17 and five yards before capping the 
drive with a seven-yard bootleg for the score. 
</P>
<P>
 Taft kept Lins under pressure throughout the first half. Linebacker Emon 
Afshar snuffed one drive with a third-down sack. 
</P>
<P>
 Lins was sacked again by Dion Gaston on third down early in the second 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Solorzano caught 10 passes for 96 yards. DeFinney caught six for 69 yards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Prep Sports; Game Story 
</P>
