<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL / SATURDAY PULLOUT; LA MIRADA QUARTERBACK LEADS ROUT OF SUNNY 
HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RUSSELL BANKS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The way La Mirada quarterback Mike Palumbo threw the football Friday night, 
the Sunny Hills defense probably thought he was unstoppable. 
</P>
<P>
 Palumbo, a 6-foot-1, 180-pound senior, completed 13 of 21 for 145 yards and 
two touchdowns as the Matadors beat Sunny Hills, 42-20, at La Mirada High in 
the season-opener for both teams. 
</P>
<P>
 And Palumbo only played the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 He strained his shoulder in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 La Mirada Coach John Mele said: "One of their big tackles landed on his (left) 
shoulder." 
</P>
<P>
 Not before Palumbo put some hurt on Sunny Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 He threw touchdowns of 27 yards to Wyatt Boatwright in the first quarter and 
17 yards to Greg Rudiger late in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Hugo Corral scored the Matadors' first touchdown on a two-yard run, after he 
returned a Sunny Hills punt 39 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers only score of the first half came on a 56-yard pass from Greg 
Garand to Jeff Renaud. 
</P>
<P>
 Garand completed 13 of 28 passes for 256 yards passing and three touchdowns. 
Two of his passes were intercepted, one of which was returned 42 yards by Ken 
Harrington for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Garand's threw a 94-yard touchdown pass to Renaud and a 16-yard touchdowns to 
tight end Sean Granillo. 
</P>
<P>
 Renaud caught five passes for 185 yards. RUSSELL BANKS 
</P>
</TEXT>
