<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; BIRMINGHAM DEFENSE STIFFENS IN VICTORY OVER 
CANOGA PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PETER WOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Quarterback Courtney Blunt scored on a 53-yard run, and the Birmingham High 
defense stopped a two-point conversion attempt in the final minute to secure a 
13-12 victory over Canoga Park in a season-opening game Friday night at 
Birmingham. 
</P>
<P>
 All the scoring in the nonleague game came in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Canoga Park nearly pulled out the game when quarterback Chris Monzon tossed an 
18-yard touchdown pass to Brandon Horn with 49 seconds to play to move the 
Hunters within one point. 
</P>
<P>
 However, Birmingham stopped a two-point conversion run by Roger Sanchez to 
preserve the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Blunt led all rushers with 72 yards in 11 carries. Monzon completed nine of 19 
passes for 150 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Canoga Park scored first on a six-yard run by Sanchez, capping a 52-yard 
drive.  
</P>
<P>
 After Blunt's run tied the score, 6-6, Birmingham increased the lead to 13-6 
on a three-yard run by Marvin Powell in the fourth quarter. PETER WOON 
</P>
</TEXT>
