<HEADLINE>
<P>
MACLEAN'S ARM LIFTS GRANADA HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BRESNAHAN, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Quarterback Brian MacLean passed for 197 yards and four touchdowns and sparked 
a 29-point second quarter as Granada Hills High rolled to a 49-13 victory 
Friday night over Monroe. 
</P>
<P>
 MacLean connected on 12 of 16 passes, including a 13-yard touchdown toss to 
Eric Carpenter that gave the Highlanders a 21-7 lead in the second period. 
</P>
<P>
 Running back Eric Richardson pitched in with two touchdown runs -- both in the 
second quarter -- and finished with 43 yards in seven carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Carpenter finished with seven catches for 128 yards and two touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Richardson's one-yard scoring run, followed by his reception on the ensuing 
two-point conversion, capped a seven-play, 70-yard drive and gave the 
Highlanders a 14-7 lead in the first period. 
</P>
<P>
 Late in the third period, a toddler fell approximately 20 feet from the top of 
the bleachers. He was rushed to Northridge Hospital because of multiple head 
injuries. Friday's Yardstick 
</P>
