<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RON STAPP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Littlerock 14, Serrano 14 -- Michael Carmona, Serrano's tailback, fumbled on a 
fourth-and-goal play from the one-yard line with 33 seconds to play to enable 
Littlerock to hang on for the tie at Antelope Valley High. 
</P>
<P>
 Serrano rallied from a 14-0 deficit to tie the score on a six-yard pass from 
Russell Anderson to Hobie Jarrard with 1:51 left in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Littlerock tailback Devin Benjamin rushed for 125 yards in 15 carries, 
including a five-yard touchdown run on the Lobos' second play from scrimmage. 
</P>
<P>
 Anderson passed for 126 yards and two touchdowns, completing 13 of 18 passes. 
Carmona rushed for 65 yards in 19 carries. RON STAPP 
</P>
</TEXT>
