<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE JOHNSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Newbury Park 18, Hueneme 6 -- Hal Sullivan intercepted a pass with 25 seconds 
to play and returned it 55 yards for a touchdown to ensure a Newbury Park 
victory at Hueneme. 
</P>
<P>
 Running back Brock Diediker, a junior, rushed for 56 yards and two touchdowns 
in 14 carries.Teammate Tony Robertson rushed for a game-high 161 yards in 24 
carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Running back Ronnie Jenkins led Hueneme with 90 yards in 19 carries. His 
27-yard touchdown run in the first quarter tied the score, 6-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Junior quarterback Justin Vint completed three of eight passes for 39 yards 
with no interceptions for Newbury Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park, the defending Division III champion, posted its 15th consecutive 
victory. The Panthers defeated Hueneme, 73-6, last season. MIKE JOHNSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
