<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BARTLETT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Burbank 28, Hoover 0 -- Opportunistic Burbank returned two fumbles for 
touchdowns and parlayed six Hoover turnovers into a victory at Glendale High. 
</P>
<P>
 Vaughn Lucas returned the first of three fumbles by Tornado quarterback Carlos 
Valadez for a 26-yard score. 
</P>
<P>
 Valadez fumbled on Hoover's next possession as well, setting up another 
Burbank touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Jason Jonas found Carlos Baker open over the middle on the first play for a 
19-yard touchdown and a 14-0 lead. Jonas completed 10 of 17 passes for 126 
yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank's Justin Cabral intercepted two passes in the second half, and Ansen 
Beck returned a third Valadez fumble 68 yards for a score in the second 
quarter. MIKE BARTLETT 
</P>
