<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; WITH STIFLING DEFENSE, ANTELOPE VALLEY POSTS 
8-0 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JIM LONG 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jermaine Lewis scored on a 16-yard run in the first quarter and Antelope 
Valley High made it hold up for an 8-0 victory over Hesperia on Friday night in 
a Southern Section nonleague opener. 
</P>
<P>
 The game was the first played at Jay Reed Field at Sultana High in Hesperia. 
</P>
<P>
 Justin Reinier scored on a run off tackle for the two-point conversion after 
Lewis scored with 3:33 to play in the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Lewis, a 5-foot-7, 155-pound junior tailback, rushed 18 times for 130 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley, which advanced to the Division I semifinals last season, 
played exceptional defense. 
</P>
<P>
 Linebacker Chad Murphy sacked Hesperia quarterback Matt Lewallen for an 
11-yard loss on a critical third down on the Scorpions' final possession. 
</P>
<P>
 The play took Hesperia from the Antelope Valley 22 to the 33 with 42 seconds 
left. On fourth down, Perry Highfill dropped a pass near the first-down marker 
and Antelope Valley took over on downs. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley quarterback Trymon Redick carried seven times for 46 yards, 
playing all but one drive in the second half with a dislocated middle finger on 
his throwing hand. 
</P>
<P>
 Redick threw only one pass, and it was incomplete. 
</P>
<P>
 Defensive lineman Anthony Borda recovered a fumble and had a sack for Antelope 
Valley and linebacker Luis Perez also recovered a fumble. JIM LONG 
</P>
</TEXT>
