<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; INTERSECTIONAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARIN ESPER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Burroughs 14, Fairfax 12 -- Floyd Nolan blocked a 39-yard field-goal attempt 
with 3:42 to play to preserve the victory in Coach Robert dos Remedios' debut. 
</P>
<P>
 Burroughs quarterback Scott Boldvich completed five of 13 for 49 yards and two 
touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Boldvich hit Tony Listro with an eight-yard touchdown pass in the first 
quarter to cap a 14-play, 79-yard drive to give Burroughs a 7-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Burroughs scored on a four-yard pass from Boldvich to Mike Barrett midway 
through the third quarter to cap a five-play, 51-yard drive and give Burroughs 
a 14-6 lead. The drive was set up by a 38-yard kick return by Ken Knoop to open 
the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlos Moreno gained 127 yards in 23 carries for Burroughs. 
</P>
<P>
 Fairfax scored with 8:33 to play to cut the Burroughs' lead to 14-12. 
</P>
<P>
 Offensive pass interference was called on the two-point conversion attempt. 
DARIN ESPER 
</P>
</TEXT>
