<TEXT>
<P>
 In other nonleague openers: 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley 28, La Canada 0 -- Running back Chris Hedrick rushed for 76 
yards in 19 carries and scored three first-half touchdowns to lead the Falcons 
at La Canada High. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback John Watts, who completed six of nine passes for 134 yards and two 
touchdowns, connected with Hedrick on a 74-yard touchdown pass one play after 
Danny Allen's interception in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Hedrick followed with touchdown runs of eight yards and one yard in the second 
quarter to put the Falcons ahead, 21-0. Watts then passed to fullback Tim 
Condie for a six-yard touchdown moments before halftime to finish the scoring. 
</P>
<P>
 La Canada quarterback James Wolstenholme connected on 11 of 17 passes for 130 
yards, but threw two interceptions. JIM TEMMEL 
