<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL / SATURDAY PULLOUT; WEST COVINA, BROWN RUN OVER KATELLA, 26-13 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DALE RUHE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Junior running back Kevin Brown rushed for 166 yards and scored one touchdown 
to lead West Covina to a 26-13 victory over Katella in the season opener Friday 
night at West Covina High. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown gave West Covina the lead for good with a 51-yard run with less than a 
minute to go in the first quarter.Katella grabbed an early 7-0 lead when James 
Henderson blocked a punt by West Covina's Terrance Spencer, and Javier Espinoza 
recovered the ball in the end zone for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Henry Frank scored the Bulldogs' first touchdown on their next 
series on a 24-yard run. Espinoza recovered a fumble by Brown at the West 
Covina 15-yard line late in the first half, but the Bulldogs stopped Katella's 
Dustin Gotz on a fourth-and-two play to preserve the the lead going into 
halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Burke opened the second half for West Covina with a 92-yard kickoff 
return for a touchdown. Greg Wardlaw capped the scoring for West Covina with a 
five-yard touchdown run with just over 10 minutes remaining in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Sal Viramontes scored on a two-yard touchdown run with just under 
two minutes left in the game. He completed key first-down passes of 16 and 26 
yards to Josh Welton prior to scoring the touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 West Covina outgained Katella in total offense, 341 yards to 159. The Bulldogs 
held Katella to 61 yards in the first half and did not allow the Knights a 
first down in the third quarter. DALE RUHE 
</P>
</TEXT>
