PREP FOOTBALL / SATURDAY PULLOUT; LONG BEACH JORDAN ROLLS OVER SANTA ANA, 47-16 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lajuan Gibbons rushed for 97 yards in 20 carries and scored two touchdowns to 
lead Long Beach Jordan to a 47-16 victory over Santa Ana Friday at Santa Ana 
Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Gibbons was the key in Long Beach Jordan's rushing attack, which overpowered 
and wore down the Santa Ana defense and gained 213 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach started the scoring when Kason Smith returned the opening kickoff 
92 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana answered when Brian Schwalm threw 39 yards to Carlos Rodriguez. 
Eddie Contreras added the extra point, and a few minutes later Contreras made a 
27-yard field goal to give Santa Ana the lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach Jordan then scored six unanswered touchdowns. Quarterback Ortega 
Jenkins threw 34 yards to Raheen Elliot for one touchdown then added two 
four-yard runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Gibbons then ran in from one and eight yards to put Long Beach Jordan up 
47-10. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose Sagrero finished the scoring when he caught a 20-yard pass from Schwalm 
late in the fourth quarter for the game's final score. JOE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
