</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANDY EISER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Che Holloway and Dan Young each scored two touchdowns as Orange Lutheran 
rolled to a 47-7 nonleague victory over San Bernardino Aquinas at Brea-Olinda 
High. 
</P>
<P>
 Holloway, a junior transfer from Tustin, ripped off a 51-yard run on the 
game's first play from scrimmage, then scored on his next two carries to give 
the Lancers a 16-0 lead with 6 minutes 22 seconds remaining in the first 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 After Matt Stratton kicked his second field goal to open the second quarter, 
Young then rushed 17 yards for a touchdown and returned a punt for 53 yards and 
a touchdown to make it 33-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Jason McQueen led the Falcons in rushing with 60 yards in 16 carries, but had 
two key fumbles as Aquinas lost the schools' first-ever meeting. ANDY EISER 
