<P>
PREP FOOTBALL / SATURDAY PULLOUT; CHAMBERS LEADS WESTERN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By COREY LYONS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dean Chambers passed for 104 yards and a touchdown, and had a rushing score, 
enabling Western to defeat Loara, 24-7, in front of 900 spectators at Glover 
Stadium Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Western utilized a conservative running game to defeat the Saxons, but 
Chambers, who completed only six of 12 with two interceptions, made the big 
plays in the clutch. 
</P>
<P>
 Western opened the game's scoring in the first quarter on an eight-yard run by 
David Bell. Then, midway through the second quarter, Chambers finished a 
seven-play, 80-yard drive with a two-yard plunge that put Western up, 14-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Western scored its final touchdown at 9:16 in the third quarter when Chambers 
hit tight end Vince Branstetter on a nine-yard scoring pass. The touchdown 
finished a four-play, 62-yard drive highlighted by a 38-yard run by Matt 
Frembling. 
</P>
<P>
 Loara's score came at 1:57 in the third quarter on a five-yard touchdown pass 
from Jim Kirkland to Aaron Beverly. The score finished a 17-play, 80-yard 
drive, the Saxons' only legitimate drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Kirkland completed nine of 30 passes for 72 yards with one interception. COREY 
LYONS 
</P>
