<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN FELLED BY ARIZONA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Missy Clements had a match-high 23 kills and teammate Aimee Stone added 16 
kills, but the Cal State Northridge women's volleyball team lost to 17th-ranked 
Arizona in the San Diego State tournament Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Arizona's 15-12, 15-9, 14-16, 16-14 victory was Northridge's second loss in a 
row, but it was an improvement over Wednesday, when 15th-ranked USC swept the 
Matadors, 15-12, 15-10, 15-8. 
</P>
<P>
 Clements' season-high 23 kills gave her 93 for the season and moved her into 
third on the all-time Northridge career list with 996. 
</P>
<P>
 Stone added 16 digs and four total blocks for Northridge (3-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Heather Anderson had eight kills and 10 digs for the Matadors while Kathleen 
Shannon contributed 47 assists and 12 digs. 
</P>
<P>
 Arizona (2-1) was led by Melissa Harris and Barb Bell. 
</P>
<P>
 Harris had 22 kills, 12 digs and four total blocks, while Bell added 20 kills 
-- on a .375 hitting percentage -- and 13 digs. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge will play San Diego State and Hofstra in its final two matches of 
the tournament today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
