<P>
A LITTLE BIT OF HISTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Behind the hitting of Roger Hanson and the pitching of Chuck Yeager, Rio Mesa 
High won the Southern Section 1-A Division baseball title in 1980. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Prep Sports 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA091094-0294 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 077849 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
September 10, 1994, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
