<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. RELIGION NOTES / DAYE CLARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAYE CLARK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rev. Diana Heath will give her first sermon as minister of the Orange 
Coast Unitarian Universalist Church in Costa Mesa on Sunday at 10:30 a.m. Her 
sermon is titled "To Say Hello." She will offer a free adult religious 
education course, "Writing Your Spiritual Autobiography, " beginning Oct. 3 at 
7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 She was formerly the minister at St. John's Unitarian Church in Cincinnati. 
The church is at 1259 Victoria St. Information: (714) 646-4652. 
</P>
</TEXT>
